systems because they

01:00:09.540 --> 01:00:12.810
want to be able to disperse
social benefits to the intended

01:00:12.810 --> 01:00:16.300
beneficiaries without exposing
them to the horrors of check

01:00:16.300 --> 01:00:19.940
cashing locations, which
are surrounded by casinos

01:00:19.940 --> 01:00:22.750
and bordellos and people who
are trying to steal their money.

01:00:22.750 --> 01:00:25.900
Instead, they drop the money
into biometrically activated

01:00:25.900 --> 01:00:28.790
cards or phones as
payment devices.

01:00:28.790 --> 01:00:30.170
It's very efficient.

01:00:30.170 --> 01:00:32.342
And it gets rid of
all the frictions, 25%

01:00:32.342 --> 01:00:33.800
to cash a check
and all that stuff.

01:00:33.800 --> 01:00:35.490
It's gone.

01:00:35.490 --> 01:00:39.580
Other countries
implement payment systems

01:00:39.580 --> 01:00:42.530
because they want to
enhance tax collection.

01:00:42.530 --> 01:00:45.620
The Koreans understand
that their people will not

01:00:45.620 --> 01:00:50.570
declare taxes honestly, and
so 93% of commerce in Korea,

01:00:50.570 --> 01:00:53.540
by mandate, is being done
through payment systems, not

01:00:53.540 --> 01:00:54.500
cash.

01:00:54.500 --> 01:00:56.984
They just don't
trust their citizens.

01:00:56.984 --> 01:00:58.400
And the way you
get around that is

01:00:58.400 --> 01:01:02.160
to have a taxable audit that's
part of the MasterCard record.

01:01:02.160 --> 01:01:04.520
And so we have all
sorts of products

01:01:04.520 --> 01:01:08.380
that are high technology
payment systems using all sorts

01:01:08.380 --> 01:01:11.030
of phones and other devices.

01:01:11.030 --> 01:01:12.840
And there's just a
general movement.

01:01:12.840 --> 01:01:16.930
And since I'm oriented
with the belief

01:01:16.930 --> 01:01:19.510
